      {
        "heading": "What is Spatial Memory?",
        "content": "Spatial memory is your brain's ability to remember where things are located. It's one of the oldest and most robust memory systems in the human brain — evolved over millions of years for survival (remembering where food, water, and danger are located). This same system can be harnessed for learning anything: vocabulary, medical terms, historical dates, or programming concepts."
