        "heading": "Why It Works Better Than Traditional Flashcards",
        "content": "Traditional flashcards are one-dimensional — you see a front, recall the back. Spatial flashcards add a second dimension: position. When you place a card at a specific location on a grid, your brain encodes both the content AND the location. During recall, the location acts as an additional retrieval cue, making it easier to access the memory. Research shows that spatial context can improve recall by 20-40% compared to non-spatial methods."
