        "heading": "Aphantasia and Spatial Memory",
        "content": "A critical finding: spatial memory works WITHOUT mental visualization. Bainbridge et al. (2021, Cortex 135) showed aphantasics have deficits in object memory but spatial accuracy is identical to controls, with fewer errors. Dawes et al. (2020, Scientific Reports 10) found spatial imagery was the only sensory domain with no significant difference from controls. Monzel et al. (2024, Cognition 251) showed aphantasics prefer non-visual spatial strategies that are equally effective as visual strategies — a third category beyond 'visual vs verbal.' This means spatial memory tools work for everyone — including the estimated 4% of the population with aphantasia (~320M people globally)."
